I hope everybody's having a

00:00:29.526 --> 00:00:31.306 A:middle
great WWDC so far and that some

00:00:31.306 --> 00:00:33.026 A:middle
of you managed to go see Todd's

00:00:33.026 --> 00:00:34.626 A:middle
talk just a little bit ago, he's

00:00:34.626 --> 00:00:35.796 A:middle
a great speaker and an

00:00:35.796 --> 00:00:37.406 A:middle
all-around awesome dude, so I

00:00:37.406 --> 00:00:38.226 A:middle
hope you enjoyed that.

00:00:39.116 --> 00:00:42.166 A:middle
My name is Skylar Peterson, I am

00:00:42.166 --> 00:00:43.676 A:middle
a member of Apple's iOS

00:00:43.676 --> 00:00:45.596 A:middle
Accessibility Team and I'm here

00:00:45.596 --> 00:00:46.946 A:middle
today to talk to you about

00:00:47.286 --> 00:00:48.486 A:middle
what's new in accessibility this

00:00:48.486 --> 00:00:48.656 A:middle
year.

00:00:50.576 --> 00:00:52.246 A:middle
So, for those of you that don't

00:00:52.246 --> 00:00:53.936 A:middle
know exactly what I mean when I

00:00:53.936 --> 00:00:56.046 A:middle
say accessibility well first of

00:00:56.046 --> 00:00:57.456 A:middle
all, I'm happy that you're here

00:00:58.076 --> 00:01:00.366 A:middle
and second, when we think about

00:01:00.366 --> 00:01:03.266 A:middle
Accessibility it's really making

00:01:03.266 --> 00:01:06.016 A:middle
technology usable by everyone

00:01:06.366 --> 00:01:07.536 A:middle
regardless of whatever their

00:01:07.536 --> 00:01:08.996 A:middle
unique needs might be.

00:01:09.396 --> 00:01:11.776 A:middle
At Apple, we approach this

00:01:11.776 --> 00:01:14.106 A:middle
problem by examining four major

00:01:14.106 --> 00:01:16.116 A:middle
classes of user ability,

00:01:17.516 --> 00:01:19.816 A:middle
cognitive, motor, vision and

00:01:19.816 --> 00:01:19.966 A:middle
hearing.

00:01:25.056 --> 00:01:27.206 A:middle
Cognitive encompasses conditions

00:01:27.786 --> 00:01:30.106 A:middle
like dyslexia or autism.

00:01:32.186 --> 00:01:34.166 A:middle
Motor examines the way in which

00:01:34.166 --> 00:01:35.806 A:middle
a user physically interacts with

00:01:35.806 --> 00:01:37.556 A:middle
the system, whether they need

00:01:37.556 --> 00:01:38.836 A:middle
special accommodations for a

00:01:38.836 --> 00:01:40.506 A:middle
condition like Parkinson's or

00:01:40.506 --> 00:01:41.346 A:middle
cerebral palsy.

00:01:43.906 --> 00:01:46.946 A:middle
Vision which encompasses a range

00:01:46.976 --> 00:01:48.966 A:middle
of visionability from those with

00:01:48.966 --> 00:01:51.016 A:middle
low vision conditions to those

00:01:51.016 --> 00:01:52.006 A:middle
who are completely blind.

00:01:53.646 --> 00:01:56.016 A:middle
And finally hearing which like

00:01:56.016 --> 00:01:59.006 A:middle
vision encompasses a spectrum of

00:01:59.056 --> 00:02:01.146 A:middle
hearing ability from those who

00:02:01.146 --> 00:02:02.946 A:middle
are hard of hearing to those

00:02:02.946 --> 00:02:06.326 A:middle
that are completely deaf.

00:02:06.776 --> 00:02:09.176 A:middle
Worldwide there are over a

00:02:09.176 --> 00:02:11.756 A:middle
billion people who have some

00:02:11.756 --> 00:02:13.236 A:middle
form of disability that fit into

00:02:13.236 --> 00:02:14.416 A:middle
one of those categories.

00:02:15.426 --> 00:02:17.996 A:middle
Put another way, one in seven,

00:02:18.926 --> 00:02:21.626 A:middle
one in seven people have a form

00:02:21.626 --> 00:02:23.886 A:middle
of disability which means that

00:02:23.886 --> 00:02:25.786 A:middle
you're going to have and already

00:02:25.786 --> 00:02:27.806 A:middle
do have users that have a

00:02:27.806 --> 00:02:28.506 A:middle
disability.

00:02:29.626 --> 00:02:30.736 A:middle
But at the end of the day

00:02:30.806 --> 00:02:32.436 A:middle
accessibility isn't about

00:02:32.436 --> 00:02:35.536 A:middle
numbers it's about people.

00:02:37.026 --> 00:02:38.476 A:middle
Accessibility is about the way

00:02:38.476 --> 00:02:39.846 A:middle
in which people interact with

00:02:39.846 --> 00:02:40.256 A:middle
the world.

00:02:42.256 --> 00:02:44.146 A:middle
It's about technology's

00:02:44.146 --> 00:02:46.776 A:middle
transformative power to enable.

00:02:49.026 --> 00:02:50.296 A:middle
It's about expanding the

00:02:50.296 --> 00:02:52.706 A:middle
possibilities of what people can

00:02:52.706 --> 00:02:52.986 A:middle
do.

