00:05:20.166 --> 00:05:21.346 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So, we've gone about tackling

00:05:21.346 --> 00:05:23.166 A:middle
problems that people like Shane

00:05:23.166 --> 00:05:25.176 A:middle
face every day by creating a

00:05:25.176 --> 00:05:27.666 A:middle
wide array of baked in

00:05:27.776 --> 00:05:30.326 A:middle
system-level features across all

00:05:30.326 --> 00:05:31.396 A:middle
of our platforms.

00:05:32.646 --> 00:05:34.056 A:middle
Which includes making sure that

00:05:34.056 --> 00:05:36.396 A:middle
our software works well with an

00:05:36.396 --> 00:05:37.306 A:middle
assortment of hardware

00:05:37.306 --> 00:05:39.326 A:middle
accessories made specifically

00:05:39.326 --> 00:05:41.006 A:middle
for people with disabilities.

00:05:41.646 --> 00:05:45.016 A:middle
But at the end of the day what

00:05:45.016 --> 00:05:46.756 A:middle
really makes Apple's platforms

00:05:46.756 --> 00:05:49.466 A:middle
great is the work that people

00:05:49.466 --> 00:05:51.976 A:middle
like you do every day to make

00:05:51.976 --> 00:05:54.216 A:middle
sure that all of those amazing

00:05:54.216 --> 00:05:55.896 A:middle
bits of content that you work on

00:05:56.336 --> 00:05:57.546 A:middle
work for everyone.

00:05:58.626 --> 00:06:01.276 A:middle
So, with that in mind, let's

00:06:01.276 --> 00:06:03.176 A:middle
take a look at what we're going

00:06:03.176 --> 00:06:03.936 A:middle
to talk about today.

00:06:04.906 --> 00:06:06.496 A:middle
The first thing I'd like to do

00:06:06.736 --> 00:06:07.916 A:middle
is highlight some of our new

00:06:07.916 --> 00:06:09.316 A:middle
assistive features across all of

00:06:09.316 --> 00:06:10.206 A:middle
our platforms.

00:06:10.706 --> 00:06:12.526 A:middle
And from there I'd like to shift

00:06:12.826 --> 00:06:14.916 A:middle
to talking about what you as a

00:06:14.916 --> 00:06:17.086 A:middle
developer can do to make sure

00:06:17.086 --> 00:06:19.076 A:middle
that your stuff works with our

00:06:19.076 --> 00:06:19.586 A:middle
stuff.

00:06:20.296 --> 00:06:22.136 A:middle
And that really starts by

00:06:22.136 --> 00:06:23.686 A:middle
auditing your own app for

00:06:23.686 --> 00:06:25.586 A:middle
accessibility, looking at what

00:06:25.586 --> 00:06:26.866 A:middle
the current accessibility

00:06:26.866 --> 00:06:28.046 A:middle
experience is like.

00:06:29.596 --> 00:06:31.116 A:middle
And from there we're going to

00:06:31.116 --> 00:06:32.136 A:middle
take a look at some of the

00:06:32.136 --> 00:06:34.116 A:middle
basics of our accessibility API

00:06:34.116 --> 00:06:36.476 A:middle
and the way that you can take

00:06:36.476 --> 00:06:38.246 A:middle
advantage of it to solve some of

00:06:38.246 --> 00:06:39.586 A:middle
the issues you find during your

00:06:40.386 --> 00:06:40.506 A:middle
audit.

00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.576 A:middle
From there we're going to go

00:06:43.576 --> 00:06:45.066 A:middle
beyond the basics to look at

00:06:45.066 --> 00:06:46.736 A:middle
some of our more advanced APIs

00:06:46.736 --> 00:06:48.216 A:middle
to help you solve some common

00:06:48.216 --> 00:06:49.466 A:middle
problems that you might find

00:06:50.046 --> 00:06:51.016 A:middle
while making your own apps

00:06:51.016 --> 00:06:51.556 A:middle
accessible.

00:06:51.626 --> 00:06:55.416 A:middle
And finally, I'd like to spend a

00:06:55.416 --> 00:06:57.306 A:middle
little bit of time talking about

00:06:57.306 --> 00:06:58.126 A:middle
some accessibility

00:06:58.126 --> 00:06:59.256 A:middle
considerations that you should

00:06:59.256 --> 00:07:01.526 A:middle
make when implementing the

00:07:01.526 --> 00:07:03.746 A:middle
drag-and-drop in iOS 11.

00:07:04.986 --> 00:07:05.896 A:middle
So, let's get started.

00:07:07.276 --> 00:07:09.926 A:middle
The first feature I'd like to

00:07:09.926 --> 00:07:11.786 A:middle
talk about today is text

00:07:11.786 --> 00:07:12.286 A:middle
detection.

00:07:13.196 --> 00:07:15.566 A:middle
So, let's imagine for a second

00:07:15.946 --> 00:07:17.676 A:middle
that you're a VoiceOver user

00:07:18.396 --> 00:07:20.376 A:middle
who's blind and you're scrolling

00:07:20.376 --> 00:07:22.086 A:middle
through your favorite social

00:07:22.086 --> 00:07:23.806 A:middle
media app and you come across an

00:07:23.806 --> 00:07:25.596 A:middle
image like this where somebody

00:07:25.886 --> 00:07:27.526 A:middle
has embedded text within an

00:07:27.526 --> 00:07:27.926 A:middle
image.

00:07:28.606 --> 00:07:29.346 A:middle
When you tap on it you're

00:07:29.346 --> 00:07:30.866 A:middle
probably not going to hear a

00:07:30.866 --> 00:07:32.216 A:middle
description of what's actually

00:07:32.216 --> 00:07:33.136 A:middle
in the image unless the

00:07:33.136 --> 00:07:34.456 A:middle
developer has gone through and

00:07:34.456 --> 00:07:36.566 A:middle
done the work to put a label

00:07:36.566 --> 00:07:37.726 A:middle
that describes it to you.

00:07:37.986 --> 00:07:41.656 A:middle
But this year in iOS 11, as well

00:07:41.656 --> 00:07:45.166 A:middle
as on macOS if you focus on an

00:07:45.166 --> 00:07:46.756 A:middle
image we're going to do some

00:07:46.756 --> 00:07:48.306 A:middle
basic text detection to try and

00:07:48.306 --> 00:07:49.776 A:middle
figure out if there's text

00:07:49.776 --> 00:07:51.416 A:middle
within that image and if it

00:07:51.416 --> 00:07:52.636 A:middle
makes sense to speak it then

00:07:52.636 --> 00:07:53.986 A:middle
we're going to speak to the user

00:07:54.066 --> 00:07:55.836 A:middle
and it sounds a little something

00:07:55.836 --> 00:07:57.016 A:middle
like this.

00:07:57.406 --> 00:07:58.956 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Possible text, I can't

00:07:58.956 --> 00:08:00.276 A:middle
believe I took this with my

00:08:00.396 --> 00:08:00.886 A:middle
iPhone.

00:08:01.556 --> 00:08:04.396 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Now along that same vein,

00:08:04.686 --> 00:08:06.526 A:middle
we're introducing improved photo

00:08:06.526 --> 00:08:08.576 A:middle
descriptions for VoiceOver users

00:08:08.856 --> 00:08:09.816 A:middle
systemwide.

00:08:10.536 --> 00:08:12.346 A:middle
So, when a VoiceOver user

00:08:12.346 --> 00:08:14.686 A:middle
focuses on an image we're going

00:08:14.686 --> 00:08:16.696 A:middle
to run some basic analysis to

00:08:16.696 --> 00:08:17.756 A:middle
try and figure out what's

00:08:17.756 --> 00:08:19.926 A:middle
contained within that image and

00:08:19.926 --> 00:08:21.966 A:middle
speak details about it so that

00:08:22.096 --> 00:08:23.706 A:middle
VoiceOver users get a richer

00:08:23.896 --> 00:08:24.446 A:middle
description.

00:08:25.306 --> 00:08:26.736 A:middle
We look for things like the

00:08:26.736 --> 00:08:28.436 A:middle
number of faces within an image,

00:08:28.846 --> 00:08:29.906 A:middle
what expressions are they

00:08:29.906 --> 00:08:32.066 A:middle
making, what's the overall scene

00:08:32.066 --> 00:08:33.576 A:middle
of that image, and what's its

00:08:33.576 --> 00:08:34.956 A:middle
blurriness or brightness level.

00:08:35.666 --> 00:08:36.996 A:middle
So, a description for an image

00:08:36.996 --> 00:08:38.636 A:middle
like this one might sound like

00:08:38.636 --> 00:08:38.966 A:middle
this.

00:08:40.366 --> 00:08:42.376 A:middle
&gt;&gt; One face, one smiling,

00:08:42.696 --> 00:08:44.736 A:middle
nightclub, blurry, bright.

00:08:45.866 --> 00:08:47.206 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Now if you're a developer

00:08:47.206 --> 00:08:48.406 A:middle
who's already gone through and

00:08:48.406 --> 00:08:49.766 A:middle
done your due diligence of

00:08:49.766 --> 00:08:51.316 A:middle
labeling all your images don't

00:08:51.316 --> 00:08:52.646 A:middle
worry we're not just going to

00:08:52.856 --> 00:08:54.436 A:middle
hijack that description from

00:08:54.436 --> 00:08:54.676 A:middle
you.

00:08:55.266 --> 00:08:57.416 A:middle
Instead, if a user wants to hear

00:08:57.416 --> 00:08:58.486 A:middle
the description that we

00:08:58.486 --> 00:09:00.146 A:middle
ourselves have generated that

00:09:00.146 --> 00:09:01.456 A:middle
all they need to do is a single

00:09:01.456 --> 00:09:02.886 A:middle
three-finger tap on the image

00:09:03.216 --> 00:09:03.976 A:middle
and they'll hear our

00:09:03.976 --> 00:09:04.486 A:middle
description.

00:09:08.796 --> 00:09:11.186 A:middle
Next, we have large texts.

00:09:11.596 --> 00:09:13.976 A:middle
So, this year our team did an

00:09:13.976 --> 00:09:15.566 A:middle
audit of the large text

00:09:15.566 --> 00:09:18.226 A:middle
experience systemwide with a

00:09:18.226 --> 00:09:20.956 A:middle
real focus on the experience of

00:09:20.956 --> 00:09:22.926 A:middle
those users who use our largest

00:09:22.926 --> 00:09:24.616 A:middle
accessibility text sizes.

00:09:24.816 --> 00:09:26.756 A:middle
And we worked with teams across

00:09:26.756 --> 00:09:28.596 A:middle
Apple to really, really improve

00:09:28.596 --> 00:09:30.176 A:middle
this experience, which also

00:09:30.176 --> 00:09:31.796 A:middle
includes some new APIs.

00:09:32.156 --> 00:09:34.346 A:middle
Now there's a lot that I could

00:09:34.346 --> 00:09:35.506 A:middle
say about this feature.

00:09:36.126 --> 00:09:37.776 A:middle
In fact, there's so much that I

00:09:37.776 --> 00:09:39.126 A:middle
could say about this feature

