00:11:50.396 --> 00:11:51.686 A:middle
this because it's going to open

00:11:51.686 --> 00:11:54.426 A:middle
up Siri to a class of users who

00:11:54.426 --> 00:11:55.856 A:middle
are unable to use it before,

00:11:56.106 --> 00:11:57.086 A:middle
those who are nonverbal.

00:12:00.456 --> 00:12:03.206 A:middle
Finally, we have Smart Invert

00:12:03.276 --> 00:12:03.826 A:middle
Colors.

00:12:04.836 --> 00:12:07.526 A:middle
So, previously on iOS if you

00:12:07.526 --> 00:12:08.816 A:middle
enabled the invert colors

00:12:08.816 --> 00:12:10.756 A:middle
feature it would invert all the

00:12:10.756 --> 00:12:12.176 A:middle
content of your device

00:12:12.436 --> 00:12:13.576 A:middle
regardless of what kind of

00:12:13.576 --> 00:12:14.746 A:middle
content it is.

00:12:15.186 --> 00:12:16.346 A:middle
But this year we're introducing

00:12:16.346 --> 00:12:18.696 A:middle
Smart Invert Colors, which looks

00:12:18.696 --> 00:12:20.216 A:middle
at specific kinds of content

00:12:20.216 --> 00:12:23.156 A:middle
like graphics or images and

00:12:23.156 --> 00:12:24.506 A:middle
doesn't invert them so that you

00:12:24.506 --> 00:12:25.966 A:middle
can see the content as it was

00:12:25.966 --> 00:12:26.886 A:middle
actually meant to be.

00:12:27.436 --> 00:12:28.886 A:middle
Now I'd actually like to do a

00:12:28.886 --> 00:12:29.896 A:middle
demo of that feature for you

00:12:29.896 --> 00:12:29.976 A:middle
now.

00:12:41.086 --> 00:12:42.916 A:middle
