00:13:02.356 --> 00:13:04.586 A:middle
users who use invert colors that

00:13:04.586 --> 00:13:05.486 A:middle
have certain low-vision

00:13:05.486 --> 00:13:07.946 A:middle
conditions where a white UI

00:13:08.116 --> 00:13:09.496 A:middle
makes the display too difficult

00:13:09.496 --> 00:13:10.816 A:middle
to look at for prolonged periods

00:13:10.816 --> 00:13:11.186 A:middle
of time.

00:13:11.626 --> 00:13:14.836 A:middle
So, I can still see my photos as

00:13:14.836 --> 00:13:15.816 A:middle
they originally were.

00:13:17.446 --> 00:13:20.416 A:middle
Now if I go to an app like Clock

00:13:20.496 --> 00:13:22.226 A:middle
which already had a dark UI

00:13:23.316 --> 00:13:24.936 A:middle
you'll also notice that we

00:13:24.936 --> 00:13:27.296 A:middle
haven't inverted that UI to keep

00:13:27.726 --> 00:13:30.096 A:middle
the dark look around that is so

00:13:30.096 --> 00:13:31.306 A:middle
important to our invert colors

00:13:31.306 --> 00:13:31.806 A:middle
users.

00:13:32.136 --> 00:13:34.186 A:middle
Now that's just a very basic

00:13:34.186 --> 00:13:36.426 A:middle
overview of that feature and I

00:13:36.486 --> 00:13:37.476 A:middle
highly recommend that you check

00:13:37.476 --> 00:13:39.036 A:middle
it out yourself and see how it

00:13:39.036 --> 00:13:40.596 A:middle
plays around with your own apps.

