00:20:26.486 --> 00:20:28.926 A:middle
First, we had elements that were

00:20:28.926 --> 00:20:30.816 A:middle
out of order and my profile

00:20:30.816 --> 00:20:32.306 A:middle
elements didn't indicate that I

00:20:32.306 --> 00:20:34.166 A:middle
could tap on them to get to my

00:20:34.166 --> 00:20:35.626 A:middle
own profile so it really makes

00:20:35.626 --> 00:20:37.546 A:middle
sense to group them together as

00:20:37.546 --> 00:20:40.536 A:middle
a single element that acts as a

00:20:40.726 --> 00:20:40.876 A:middle
button.

00:20:41.246 --> 00:20:43.766 A:middle
Next, I have unlabeled buttons

00:20:43.896 --> 00:20:47.346 A:middle
on the top, as well as these on

00:20:47.346 --> 00:20:47.726 A:middle
the cell.

00:20:50.836 --> 00:20:52.836 A:middle
The star view was entirely

00:20:52.836 --> 00:20:57.686 A:middle
inaccessible, as was initiating

00:20:57.686 --> 00:20:58.846 A:middle
a delete of a post.

00:21:00.306 --> 00:21:03.616 A:middle
And finally, the settings didn't

00:21:03.616 --> 00:21:04.576 A:middle
tell me whether or not they were

00:21:04.576 --> 00:21:07.956 A:middle
enabled and an activate of them

00:21:07.996 --> 00:21:09.216 A:middle
didn't actually change the

00:21:10.416 --> 00:21:11.006 A:middle
value.

00:21:13.436 --> 00:21:14.316 A:middle
So, how do we solve them?

00:21:15.876 --> 00:21:17.916 A:middle
Well when a technology like

00:21:17.916 --> 00:21:20.196 A:middle
VoiceOver is trying to get

00:21:20.196 --> 00:21:21.876 A:middle
information about an element for

00:21:21.876 --> 00:21:23.186 A:middle
an app, so when a VoiceOver user

00:21:23.346 --> 00:21:24.506 A:middle
focuses on an element on the

00:21:24.506 --> 00:21:26.446 A:middle
screen it's going to ask a

00:21:26.486 --> 00:21:27.686 A:middle
couple of questions.

00:21:28.666 --> 00:21:31.126 A:middle
Questions like what are you, I'm

00:21:32.336 --> 00:21:33.606 A:middle
a button?

00:21:35.396 --> 00:21:39.786 A:middle
Who are you, I'm a Notifications

00:21:39.786 --> 00:21:40.126 A:middle
button?

00:21:41.566 --> 00:21:47.136 A:middle
What's your value, three unread

00:21:47.136 --> 00:21:47.946 A:middle
notifications?

00:21:48.946 --> 00:21:50.926 A:middle
Now all of these questions and

00:21:50.926 --> 00:21:53.586 A:middle
answers correspond to properties

00:21:53.586 --> 00:21:55.436 A:middle
in code and return specific

00:21:55.436 --> 00:21:56.576 A:middle
kinds of return values.

00:21:56.816 --> 00:21:59.736 A:middle
So, let's take a look at this.

00:22:00.316 --> 00:22:02.636 A:middle
Here we have the five basic

00:22:02.636 --> 00:22:04.666 A:middle
properties in the accessibility

00:22:04.846 --> 00:22:06.476 A:middle
protocol and we're going to go

00:22:06.476 --> 00:22:07.566 A:middle
through them one by one looking

00:22:07.566 --> 00:22:08.266 A:middle
at an example.

00:22:09.156 --> 00:22:11.016 A:middle
So, the first

00:22:11.126 --> 00:22:13.696 A:middle
isAccessibilityElement indicates

00:22:13.996 --> 00:22:15.866 A:middle
to a technology like VoiceOver

00:22:15.866 --> 00:22:17.596 A:middle
or Switch Control whether the

00:22:17.596 --> 00:22:18.856 A:middle
given element should be visible

00:22:18.856 --> 00:22:19.756 A:middle
to VoiceOver at all.

00:22:20.756 --> 00:22:23.086 A:middle
So, if we're looking at the

00:22:23.086 --> 00:22:26.536 A:middle
memory view up in the corner

00:22:26.536 --> 00:22:28.706 A:middle
there that has a slideshow of

00:22:28.706 --> 00:22:30.846 A:middle
images within the memory, a

00:22:30.846 --> 00:22:32.456 A:middle
label with the title, as well as

00:22:32.456 --> 00:22:34.066 A:middle
a play button that's a great

00:22:34.066 --> 00:22:36.996 A:middle
candidate for making a button,

00:22:37.186 --> 00:22:38.586 A:middle
the overall element a button

00:22:38.586 --> 00:22:41.356 A:middle
that when I tap on plays the

00:22:41.356 --> 00:22:41.786 A:middle
movie.

00:22:42.446 --> 00:22:44.626 A:middle
So, I'm going to set

00:22:44.906 --> 00:22:46.206 A:middle
isAccessibilityElement to be

00:22:46.206 --> 00:22:48.056 A:middle
true on that memory view.

00:22:48.576 --> 00:22:51.406 A:middle
But now because of the way that

00:22:51.406 --> 00:22:53.226 A:middle
I've coded this it's possible

00:22:53.226 --> 00:22:54.626 A:middle
that this play button is still

00:22:54.626 --> 00:22:56.316 A:middle
going to come up as an

00:22:56.396 --> 00:22:58.216 A:middle
accessible element to VoiceOver

00:22:58.526 --> 00:23:00.126 A:middle
and because I'm making that

00:23:00.126 --> 00:23:02.406 A:middle
overall element the target

00:23:02.406 --> 00:23:05.356 A:middle
instead then I want to set this

00:23:05.356 --> 00:23:06.616 A:middle
play button's is excessively

00:23:06.616 --> 00:23:08.186 A:middle
element to be false so that it

00:23:08.186 --> 00:23:09.976 A:middle
doesn't come up and we don't

00:23:09.976 --> 00:23:10.896 A:middle
have redundancy there.

00:23:11.956 --> 00:23:14.546 A:middle
And one thing that I forgot to

00:23:14.546 --> 00:23:18.216 A:middle
mention is that it's a good idea

00:23:18.216 --> 00:23:20.696 A:middle
to make the big area the play

00:23:20.696 --> 00:23:22.676 A:middle
button instead because if I'm a

00:23:22.676 --> 00:23:24.956 A:middle
VoiceOver user navigating around

00:23:25.316 --> 00:23:27.136 A:middle
this UI with by just feeling my

00:23:27.136 --> 00:23:29.096 A:middle
finger around the screen it's

00:23:29.096 --> 00:23:31.016 A:middle
much harder to find that tiny

00:23:31.016 --> 00:23:32.516 A:middle
play button to play the movie

00:23:32.516 --> 00:23:33.796 A:middle
than it is to find that big

00:23:33.846 --> 00:23:34.136 A:middle
area.

00:23:34.626 --> 00:23:39.986 A:middle
Next, we have accessibilityLabel

00:23:40.636 --> 00:23:42.326 A:middle
which describes what an element

00:23:42.356 --> 00:23:42.846 A:middle
is.

00:23:43.656 --> 00:23:45.096 A:middle
So, for example with our memory

00:23:45.096 --> 00:23:47.716 A:middle
view it's a memory and its title

00:23:47.886 --> 00:23:49.866 A:middle
is February 18th, 2017.

00:23:49.866 --> 00:23:51.516 A:middle
So, that seems like a reasonable

00:23:51.806 --> 00:23:52.146 A:middle
label.

00:23:52.746 --> 00:23:54.826 A:middle
But now because we're going to

00:23:54.826 --> 00:23:56.976 A:middle
be treating it like a button you

00:23:56.976 --> 00:23:59.206 A:middle
might wonder why we don't add

00:23:59.356 --> 00:24:01.006 A:middle
the word button into our label

00:24:01.406 --> 00:24:02.876 A:middle
and that's because of this next

00:24:02.876 --> 00:24:05.466 A:middle
property, accessibilityTraits.

00:24:06.146 --> 00:24:08.306 A:middle
This indicates to VoiceOver what

00:24:08.356 --> 00:24:10.406 A:middle
category an element fits into.

00:24:11.086 --> 00:24:13.066 A:middle
So, for example we're going to

00:24:13.066 --> 00:24:14.176 A:middle
set our memory view

00:24:14.176 --> 00:24:15.776 A:middle
accessibilityTraits to include

00:24:15.966 --> 00:24:17.136 A:middle
the button trait so that

00:24:17.136 --> 00:24:18.496 A:middle
VoiceOver knows to treat it like

00:24:18.496 --> 00:24:18.946 A:middle
a button.

00:24:19.736 --> 00:24:20.836 A:middle
This also means that when it

00:24:20.836 --> 00:24:22.056 A:middle
reads the description for the

00:24:22.056 --> 00:24:24.546 A:middle
item it's going to say button at

00:24:24.546 --> 00:24:25.906 A:middle
the end of that so that the user

00:24:25.906 --> 00:24:26.836 A:middle
knows what it is.

00:24:27.226 --> 00:24:29.656 A:middle
Now traits are also important

00:24:29.656 --> 00:24:30.596 A:middle
for two more reasons.

00:24:31.176 --> 00:24:32.966 A:middle
One, they can afford certain UI

00:24:32.966 --> 00:24:34.676 A:middle
behaviors which you'll see you

00:24:34.676 --> 00:24:35.876 A:middle
later in the presentation.

00:24:36.506 --> 00:24:39.506 A:middle
And two, there's mechanisms for

00:24:39.506 --> 00:24:42.126 A:middle
users to navigate the interface

00:24:42.186 --> 00:24:44.176 A:middle
based on specific kinds of items

00:24:44.176 --> 00:24:45.766 A:middle
that will be surfaced based on

00:24:45.766 --> 00:24:49.186 A:middle
what traits are associated with

00:24:49.826 --> 00:24:49.906 A:middle
it.

00:24:50.166 --> 00:24:52.586 A:middle
Next, we have accessibilityValue

00:24:53.146 --> 00:24:55.206 A:middle
which is for elements that have

00:24:55.206 --> 00:24:56.236 A:middle
some form of state.

00:24:56.986 --> 00:25:00.296 A:middle
So, for instance if we're in our

00:25:00.296 --> 00:25:01.996 A:middle
memory video and we're editing

00:25:02.346 --> 00:25:03.476 A:middle
there's a scrubber along the

00:25:03.476 --> 00:25:05.596 A:middle
bottom that allows me to scrub

00:25:05.596 --> 00:25:06.726 A:middle
through the whole video.

00:25:07.646 --> 00:25:09.626 A:middle
And the current valve of that

00:25:09.626 --> 00:25:12.696 A:middle
item is the second that I'm

00:25:12.696 --> 00:25:14.186 A:middle
focused on of the elapsed

00:25:14.186 --> 00:25:15.196 A:middle
seconds that have already

00:25:15.196 --> 00:25:15.666 A:middle
happened.

00:25:16.246 --> 00:25:17.586 A:middle
So, I can set its accessibility

00:25:17.586 --> 00:25:19.996 A:middle
value to be that elapsed number

00:25:19.996 --> 00:25:21.056 A:middle
of seconds that I'm currently

00:25:21.056 --> 00:25:23.126 A:middle
looking at.

00:25:23.556 --> 00:25:25.176 A:middle
Finally, we have

00:25:25.176 --> 00:25:26.896 A:middle
accessibilityHint.

00:25:27.756 --> 00:25:29.256 A:middle
Now this is meant to be a more

00:25:29.256 --> 00:25:31.446 A:middle
longform description of how to

00:25:31.446 --> 00:25:33.026 A:middle
interact with an element, what

00:25:33.026 --> 00:25:35.186 A:middle
it does or what it's meant for.

00:25:36.136 --> 00:25:39.266 A:middle
You can think of this as being a

00:25:39.266 --> 00:25:41.186 A:middle
property that allows you to

00:25:41.186 --> 00:25:42.936 A:middle
describe to a user that's new to

00:25:42.936 --> 00:25:45.056 A:middle
your interface and help them

00:25:45.056 --> 00:25:47.266 A:middle
learn how to use your interface.

00:25:47.746 --> 00:25:49.556 A:middle
But it's important that you

00:25:49.556 --> 00:25:52.316 A:middle
never put critical information

00:25:52.316 --> 00:25:55.506 A:middle
to whoever's using it in a hint

00:25:55.616 --> 00:25:56.856 A:middle
because hints can actually be

00:25:56.856 --> 00:25:58.806 A:middle
disabled to keep VoiceOver from

00:25:58.806 --> 00:26:00.166 A:middle
being too verbose for

00:26:00.166 --> 00:26:00.976 A:middle
experienced users.

00:26:08.116 --> 00:26:09.166 A:middle
So, going a little further.

00:26:09.896 --> 00:26:12.056 A:middle
New this year we have attributed

00:26:12.056 --> 00:26:14.596 A:middle
versions of label, value and

00:26:14.596 --> 00:26:14.876 A:middle
hint.

00:26:15.586 --> 00:26:17.456 A:middle
And what these allow you to do

00:26:17.456 --> 00:26:19.766 A:middle
is pass through specific keys to

00:26:19.766 --> 00:26:21.686 A:middle
tweak the way in which VoiceOver

00:26:21.876 --> 00:26:22.926 A:middle
speaks a string.

00:26:23.816 --> 00:26:25.936 A:middle
So, for example if I have a

00:26:25.936 --> 00:26:27.606 A:middle
string that I know I want to

00:26:27.606 --> 00:26:28.666 A:middle
speak -- that's in a different

00:26:28.666 --> 00:26:30.196 A:middle
language and should be spoken

00:26:30.716 --> 00:26:31.916 A:middle
with a different voice

00:26:31.916 --> 00:26:33.416 A:middle
synthesizer specific to that

00:26:33.416 --> 00:26:35.546 A:middle
language then I can use the

00:26:35.546 --> 00:26:37.036 A:middle
UIAccessibilitySpeech

00:26:37.076 --> 00:26:39.746 A:middle
AttributeLanguage key and pass

00:26:39.746 --> 00:26:41.846 A:middle
in the correct language code so

00:26:41.846 --> 00:26:43.376 A:middle
that when VoiceOver speaks it,

00:26:43.736 --> 00:26:45.556 A:middle
it speaks it with say in this

00:26:45.556 --> 00:26:47.116 A:middle
example, the French synthesizer.

00:26:49.516 --> 00:26:51.586 A:middle
Now as well let's say I had an

00:26:51.586 --> 00:26:54.736 A:middle
announcement that I wanted to

00:26:54.736 --> 00:26:57.106 A:middle
post and speak, but I felt like

00:26:57.106 --> 00:26:58.836 A:middle
that announcement isn't

00:26:58.836 --> 00:27:00.356 A:middle
important enough to interrupt

00:27:00.356 --> 00:27:01.436 A:middle
whatever current speech is

00:27:01.436 --> 00:27:01.976 A:middle
happening.

00:27:02.596 --> 00:27:03.866 A:middle
Well in this case I can use an

00:27:03.866 --> 00:27:05.526 A:middle
attributed string with the

00:27:05.526 --> 00:27:07.026 A:middle
UIAccessibilitySpeech

00:27:07.086 --> 00:27:09.276 A:middle
AttributeQueueAnnouncement that

00:27:09.276 --> 00:27:10.886 A:middle
will queue the speech behind

00:27:10.886 --> 00:27:12.026 A:middle
whatever existing speech is

00:27:12.026 --> 00:27:14.166 A:middle
already there so that it will be

00:27:14.166 --> 00:27:16.096 A:middle
spoken whatever VoiceOver was

00:27:16.096 --> 00:27:19.136 A:middle
already speaking is done.

00:27:20.036 --> 00:27:22.046 A:middle
Also, new this year we have the

00:27:22.046 --> 00:27:24.026 A:middle
concept of containers.

00:27:24.516 --> 00:27:26.406 A:middle
So previously, when a VoiceOver

00:27:26.406 --> 00:27:28.806 A:middle
user would swipe into a

00:27:28.806 --> 00:27:30.976 A:middle
container of some kind they

00:27:30.976 --> 00:27:31.626 A:middle
wouldn't really get an

00:27:31.626 --> 00:27:34.006 A:middle
indication of what kind of thing

00:27:34.006 --> 00:27:34.966 A:middle
they were swiping into, what

00:27:34.966 --> 00:27:36.516 A:middle
does those content actually even

00:27:36.516 --> 00:27:36.796 A:middle
mean.

00:27:38.066 --> 00:27:38.966 A:middle
So, we're introducing

00:27:38.966 --> 00:27:41.046 A:middle
accessibilityContainerType where

00:27:41.046 --> 00:27:43.036 A:middle
you can define this and there

00:27:43.036 --> 00:27:44.506 A:middle
are several different kinds of

00:27:44.506 --> 00:27:45.316 A:middle
containers.

00:27:46.356 --> 00:27:48.016 A:middle
The biggest one there is

00:27:48.016 --> 00:27:49.816 A:middle
dataTable which actually

00:27:49.816 --> 00:27:51.286 A:middle
requires conformance to the UI

00:27:51.286 --> 00:27:52.576 A:middle
accessibility container

00:27:52.576 --> 00:27:56.346 A:middle
dataTable protocol and improves

00:27:56.346 --> 00:27:57.756 A:middle
the way in which a VoiceOver

00:27:57.756 --> 00:27:59.126 A:middle
user can navigate through your

00:27:59.126 --> 00:28:00.726 A:middle
dataTable and understand where

00:28:02.656 --> 00:28:02.966 A:middle
they are.

00:28:03.956 --> 00:28:04.966 A:middle
So, everything that I just

00:28:04.996 --> 00:28:08.236 A:middle
covered there applies to views

00:28:08.236 --> 00:28:09.926 A:middle
that you would use through UIKit

00:28:10.346 --> 00:28:10.413 A:middle
you.

00:28:10.696 --> 00:28:14.806 A:middle
But what if your controls exist

00:28:14.806 --> 00:28:16.736 A:middle
out of UIKit, you have some sort

00:28:16.736 --> 00:28:19.026 A:middle
of non-view element that perhaps

00:28:19.026 --> 00:28:20.306 A:middle
you've drawn using core

00:28:20.306 --> 00:28:21.046 A:middle
graphics.

00:28:21.736 --> 00:28:23.346 A:middle
Well in that case we still need

00:28:23.346 --> 00:28:25.656 A:middle
to surface those controls to

00:28:25.656 --> 00:28:29.746 A:middle
VoiceOver and so we're going to

00:28:29.746 --> 00:28:33.466 A:middle
use UI accessibilityElement to

00:28:33.466 --> 00:28:35.766 A:middle
represent logical accessible

00:28:35.766 --> 00:28:37.006 A:middle
regions of the screen to

00:28:37.006 --> 00:28:39.006 A:middle
basically stand in for those

00:28:39.006 --> 00:28:39.626 A:middle
controls.

00:28:40.196 --> 00:28:42.656 A:middle
So, UI accessibilityElement you

00:28:42.656 --> 00:28:44.696 A:middle
set all the properties that I

00:28:44.696 --> 00:28:46.556 A:middle
covered before on it like you

00:28:46.556 --> 00:28:48.716 A:middle
would on any other view and it's

00:28:48.716 --> 00:28:49.666 A:middle
initialized with an

00:28:49.666 --> 00:28:51.466 A:middle
accessibility container that

00:28:51.466 --> 00:28:52.376 A:middle
would be the view that it's

00:28:52.406 --> 00:28:53.186 A:middle
contained in.

00:28:54.406 --> 00:28:56.516 A:middle
And then you override on the

00:28:56.616 --> 00:28:57.446 A:middle
container the

00:28:57.446 --> 00:28:59.266 A:middle
accessibilityElements protocol

00:28:59.986 --> 00:29:03.856 A:middle
which tells VoiceOver what sub

00:29:03.856 --> 00:29:06.516 A:middle
elements within a view are the

00:29:06.516 --> 00:29:07.566 A:middle
accessible elements.

00:29:08.316 --> 00:29:10.756 A:middle
And the order in which elements

00:29:10.756 --> 00:29:12.716 A:middle
are returned in this array is

00:29:12.716 --> 00:29:15.336 A:middle
the order in which VoiceOver

00:29:15.336 --> 00:29:16.196 A:middle
will swipe through them.

00:29:17.066 --> 00:29:19.906 A:middle
So that seems like a great

00:29:19.956 --> 00:29:22.876 A:middle
candidate for combining those

00:29:23.406 --> 00:29:24.966 A:middle
profile elements into a single

00:29:24.966 --> 00:29:25.386 A:middle
element.

00:29:26.916 --> 00:29:28.576 A:middle
So, let's come back over to our

00:29:28.576 --> 00:29:31.206 A:middle
sample app and take a look at

00:29:31.206 --> 00:29:32.006 A:middle
implementing some of these

00:29:32.006 --> 00:29:32.496 A:middle
basics.

00:29:42.246 --> 00:29:45.106 A:middle
Okay, so I have -- I'm in my

00:29:45.106 --> 00:29:46.206 A:middle
home view controller which is

00:29:46.206 --> 00:29:47.666 A:middle
the main screen I'm on and the

00:29:47.666 --> 00:29:49.706 A:middle
first I want to do is fix the

00:29:49.706 --> 00:29:52.326 A:middle
labels for those buttons that

00:29:52.326 --> 00:29:52.976 A:middle
are up on the top.

00:29:59.046 --> 00:30:00.866 A:middle
So, for the add button I'm going

00:30:00.866 --> 00:30:02.216 A:middle
to say new post because it

00:30:02.216 --> 00:30:03.196 A:middle
creates a new post.

00:30:03.856 --> 00:30:04.996 A:middle
The notifications button I'm

00:30:04.996 --> 00:30:05.856 A:middle
going to set its label to be

00:30:05.856 --> 00:30:08.506 A:middle
notifications and its value to

00:30:08.506 --> 00:30:10.266 A:middle
be my current number of unread

00:30:10.266 --> 00:30:11.286 A:middle
notifications.

00:30:11.476 --> 00:30:13.186 A:middle
And then the settings button I'm

00:30:13.186 --> 00:30:13.976 A:middle
going to set to be settings.

00:30:19.046 --> 00:30:19.926 A:middle
Now I'm going to go take care of

00:30:19.926 --> 00:30:21.676 A:middle
those other unlabeled buttons

00:30:21.976 --> 00:30:24.736 A:middle
that were my upload and download

00:30:26.426 --> 00:30:26.926 A:middle
buttons.

00:30:27.536 --> 00:30:31.276 A:middle
So, for my approved button I'm

00:30:31.276 --> 00:30:32.586 A:middle
going to set its label to be up

00:30:32.586 --> 00:30:34.256 A:middle
vote and for my disapprove

00:30:34.256 --> 00:30:35.436 A:middle
button down vote.

00:30:36.506 --> 00:30:38.216 A:middle
Now I need to also remember to

00:30:38.216 --> 00:30:40.176 A:middle
change the accessibility value

00:30:40.176 --> 00:30:42.236 A:middle
of these buttons whenever my

00:30:42.236 --> 00:30:43.556 A:middle
number of approves or number of

