00:35:15.206 --> 00:35:16.866 A:middle
Now there are a couple of

00:35:16.866 --> 00:35:18.566 A:middle
problems that we found during

00:35:18.566 --> 00:35:20.626 A:middle
our audit that we still haven't

00:35:20.626 --> 00:35:21.646 A:middle
actually fixed.

00:35:22.026 --> 00:35:23.616 A:middle
I still have no way of bringing

00:35:23.616 --> 00:35:24.536 A:middle
up the delete sheet.

00:35:24.966 --> 00:35:28.326 A:middle
I have no way of actually

00:35:28.326 --> 00:35:30.556 A:middle
changing the value of the star

00:35:30.556 --> 00:35:31.456 A:middle
rating view.

00:35:31.536 --> 00:35:34.046 A:middle
I can see what it is, I can see

00:35:34.046 --> 00:35:36.186 A:middle
what the current number stars

00:35:36.186 --> 00:35:36.976 A:middle
is, but I have no way of

00:35:36.976 --> 00:35:37.596 A:middle
changing it.

00:35:38.506 --> 00:35:40.046 A:middle
And when I double tap on my

00:35:40.046 --> 00:35:41.166 A:middle
setting it's still not changing

00:35:41.166 --> 00:35:41.926 A:middle
that setting value.

00:35:43.266 --> 00:35:45.746 A:middle
So, the first thing I want to

00:35:45.746 --> 00:35:47.886 A:middle
look at are custom actions.

00:35:48.766 --> 00:35:52.146 A:middle
So, we're going to use these to

00:35:52.146 --> 00:35:53.666 A:middle
bring up that delete sheet in

00:35:53.666 --> 00:35:54.346 A:middle
our sample app.

00:35:54.996 --> 00:35:57.126 A:middle
Basically, a custom action is

00:35:57.126 --> 00:35:58.996 A:middle
something that you add to an

00:35:58.996 --> 00:36:01.316 A:middle
element that is an action that

00:36:01.316 --> 00:36:04.286 A:middle
it has available to it.

00:36:04.286 --> 00:36:07.866 A:middle
So, views have the property

00:36:07.866 --> 00:36:09.846 A:middle
accessibilityCustomActions which

00:36:09.846 --> 00:36:11.646 A:middle
you can override with an array

00:36:12.036 --> 00:36:13.826 A:middle
of UI accessibilityCustomAction

00:36:14.336 --> 00:36:16.236 A:middle
that are all of the actions

00:36:16.236 --> 00:36:16.866 A:middle
available to it.

00:36:17.426 --> 00:36:18.376 A:middle
So, what does an action look

00:36:18.376 --> 00:36:18.576 A:middle
like?

00:36:19.426 --> 00:36:21.876 A:middle
Well it has a name for instance,

00:36:21.876 --> 00:36:23.266 A:middle
our delete action is called

00:36:23.266 --> 00:36:24.986 A:middle
delete because it tells the user

00:36:24.986 --> 00:36:27.686 A:middle
what it does and it has a target

00:36:27.686 --> 00:36:29.096 A:middle
and a selector that get called

00:36:29.146 --> 00:36:30.076 A:middle
whenever that action is

00:36:30.076 --> 00:36:30.696 A:middle
initiated.

00:36:32.106 --> 00:36:36.346 A:middle
So, when a view has custom

00:36:36.346 --> 00:36:38.606 A:middle
actions it's going to tell that

00:36:38.606 --> 00:36:41.176 A:middle
to the user and then the user

00:36:41.176 --> 00:36:42.606 A:middle
can swipe up or down with their

00:36:42.606 --> 00:36:44.836 A:middle
finger to cycle through the

00:36:44.836 --> 00:36:46.616 A:middle
current actions of that element.

00:36:46.996 --> 00:36:48.016 A:middle
And when they land on the one

00:36:48.016 --> 00:36:49.216 A:middle
that they want to activate a

00:36:49.536 --> 00:36:51.246 A:middle
double tap instead of doing

00:36:51.246 --> 00:36:52.276 A:middle
whatever the default behavior

00:36:52.276 --> 00:36:54.106 A:middle
will do will initiate that

00:36:54.106 --> 00:36:54.536 A:middle
action.

00:36:55.626 --> 00:36:57.626 A:middle
So, for instance, with our

00:36:57.626 --> 00:37:00.046 A:middle
delete we can create a custom

00:37:00.046 --> 00:37:02.106 A:middle
action called delete, set our

00:37:02.106 --> 00:37:04.046 A:middle
self as the target with our

00:37:04.046 --> 00:37:05.536 A:middle
delete cell action method that

00:37:05.536 --> 00:37:08.046 A:middle
returns a Boolean and that calls

00:37:08.046 --> 00:37:10.296 A:middle
the code for actually initiating

00:37:10.296 --> 00:37:11.146 A:middle
the delete of the cell.

00:37:12.346 --> 00:37:13.836 A:middle
On our cell, we're going to

00:37:13.836 --> 00:37:14.436 A:middle
override

00:37:14.436 --> 00:37:16.606 A:middle
accessibilityCustomActions to

00:37:16.606 --> 00:37:17.936 A:middle
contain this custom action.

00:37:18.626 --> 00:37:20.836 A:middle
Now because we're overriding it

00:37:20.956 --> 00:37:22.796 A:middle
on the cell and the cell itself

00:37:22.866 --> 00:37:24.356 A:middle
isn't an accessibilityElement,

00:37:24.356 --> 00:37:25.606 A:middle
all of its sub elements are.

00:37:26.276 --> 00:37:27.616 A:middle
All of its sub elements are

00:37:27.616 --> 00:37:29.246 A:middle
going to inherit the custom

00:37:29.246 --> 00:37:30.946 A:middle
actions of its parent.

00:37:31.166 --> 00:37:33.196 A:middle
So, I can actually initiate this

00:37:33.196 --> 00:37:34.956 A:middle
delete action from any of the

00:37:34.956 --> 00:37:37.996 A:middle
views on the cell.

00:37:38.946 --> 00:37:40.406 A:middle
Next, we have the default

00:37:40.406 --> 00:37:41.066 A:middle
activation.

00:37:41.296 --> 00:37:42.946 A:middle
So, what if we want to actually

00:37:42.946 --> 00:37:44.486 A:middle
override what the default

00:37:44.486 --> 00:37:46.516 A:middle
behavior is when a VoiceOver

00:37:46.516 --> 00:37:47.956 A:middle
user double taps on an element.

00:37:48.356 --> 00:37:49.626 A:middle
And that's what we're going to

00:37:49.626 --> 00:37:51.186 A:middle
use to fix the problem of

00:37:51.186 --> 00:37:53.086 A:middle
actually changing our settings.

00:37:54.756 --> 00:37:56.686 A:middle
What you can do is override

00:37:56.686 --> 00:37:58.996 A:middle
accessibilityActivate, which

00:37:58.996 --> 00:38:01.336 A:middle
returns a Boolean indicating

00:38:01.336 --> 00:38:02.806 A:middle
whether or not the activation

00:38:02.806 --> 00:38:03.506 A:middle
was successful.

00:38:05.836 --> 00:38:07.956 A:middle
So, for example with our switch

00:38:07.956 --> 00:38:10.226 A:middle
cells we can override

00:38:10.226 --> 00:38:12.626 A:middle
accessibilityActivate and set

00:38:12.626 --> 00:38:14.306 A:middle
whether or not the switch is on

00:38:14.736 --> 00:38:16.546 A:middle
based on its current on value.

00:38:16.546 --> 00:38:18.176 A:middle
And we're always going to return

00:38:18.176 --> 00:38:19.806 A:middle
true because we know that that

00:38:19.806 --> 00:38:21.096 A:middle
action is always going to be

00:38:21.096 --> 00:38:21.666 A:middle
successful.

00:38:22.126 --> 00:38:26.446 A:middle
Next, we have adjustable

00:38:26.446 --> 00:38:29.286 A:middle
elements, so our star rating is

00:38:29.286 --> 00:38:32.666 A:middle
adjustable and VoiceOver has a

00:38:32.666 --> 00:38:35.076 A:middle
mechanism for adjustable

00:38:35.076 --> 00:38:36.886 A:middle
elements to respond to increment

00:38:36.886 --> 00:38:37.816 A:middle
and decrement calls.

00:38:39.386 --> 00:38:41.956 A:middle
So, the first thing we want to

00:38:41.956 --> 00:38:43.796 A:middle
return in that element's traits

00:38:43.866 --> 00:38:45.536 A:middle
that it is an adjustable element

00:38:46.436 --> 00:38:48.296 A:middle
and that tells VoiceOver that

00:38:48.296 --> 00:38:50.056 A:middle
element is going to respond to

00:38:50.056 --> 00:38:52.156 A:middle
the accessibilityIncrement and

00:38:52.156 --> 00:38:53.966 A:middle
decrement calls which we can

00:38:53.966 --> 00:38:57.046 A:middle
override to do whatever behavior

00:38:57.046 --> 00:38:58.536 A:middle
we need when we increment and

00:38:58.536 --> 00:38:58.976 A:middle
decrement.

00:38:58.976 --> 00:39:02.486 A:middle
And a user adjusts an adjustable

00:39:02.486 --> 00:39:04.166 A:middle
element by swiping up and down

00:39:04.166 --> 00:39:04.766 A:middle
with their finger.

00:39:05.056 --> 00:39:07.626 A:middle
Up as an increment, down as a

00:39:08.336 --> 00:39:08.636 A:middle
decrement.

00:39:09.286 --> 00:39:12.066 A:middle
So, with our star's view we have

00:39:12.126 --> 00:39:13.706 A:middle
the number of stars that

00:39:13.706 --> 00:39:15.946 A:middle
whenever it's set has code that

00:39:15.946 --> 00:39:17.206 A:middle
actually adjusts the view

00:39:17.206 --> 00:39:17.916 A:middle
itself.

00:39:19.016 --> 00:39:20.516 A:middle
In its traits, we're going to

00:39:20.516 --> 00:39:22.166 A:middle
include the adjustable trait.

00:39:22.826 --> 00:39:24.846 A:middle
And in increment we're simply

00:39:24.846 --> 00:39:25.906 A:middle
going to increase the number of

00:39:25.906 --> 00:39:28.186 A:middle
stars by one and in decrement

00:39:28.186 --> 00:39:29.356 A:middle
we're going to decrease the

00:39:29.436 --> 00:39:31.156 A:middle
number of stars by one and now

00:39:31.156 --> 00:39:32.976 A:middle
that element is fully accessible

00:39:33.136 --> 00:39:34.186 A:middle
to our VoiceOver users.

00:39:35.206 --> 00:39:37.176 A:middle
Now I'd like to look at a

00:39:37.176 --> 00:39:38.416 A:middle
different problem that we didn't

00:39:38.416 --> 00:39:39.796 A:middle
see in our sample app.

00:39:40.886 --> 00:39:44.416 A:middle
So, VoiceOver has this concept

00:39:44.496 --> 00:39:46.976 A:middle
of pass-through which happens

00:39:46.976 --> 00:39:49.376 A:middle
when a VoiceOver user double

00:39:49.376 --> 00:39:51.566 A:middle
taps and holds their finger and

00:39:51.566 --> 00:39:53.846 A:middle
it passes through the panning

00:39:53.846 --> 00:39:55.986 A:middle
gesture so I can actually run my

00:39:55.986 --> 00:39:58.626 A:middle
finger across the screen and get

00:39:58.626 --> 00:40:00.016 A:middle
a more fine adjustment of a

00:40:00.016 --> 00:40:01.996 A:middle
slider like you see in this

00:40:01.996 --> 00:40:02.946 A:middle
photo's page here.

00:40:04.526 --> 00:40:06.716 A:middle
But we want a way to tell

00:40:06.716 --> 00:40:08.966 A:middle
VoiceOver where it should

00:40:08.966 --> 00:40:11.626 A:middle
actually focus that panning when

00:40:11.626 --> 00:40:13.796 A:middle
I initiate it because if I'm a

00:40:13.796 --> 00:40:16.106 A:middle
VoiceOver user then I probably

00:40:16.106 --> 00:40:19.056 A:middle
am not going to be able to

00:40:19.146 --> 00:40:21.376 A:middle
accurately land my finger on

00:40:21.376 --> 00:40:23.346 A:middle
that little sliding nub in the

00:40:23.346 --> 00:40:25.796 A:middle
center right, I don't actually

00:40:25.796 --> 00:40:27.736 A:middle
know where it is.

00:40:27.946 --> 00:40:28.796 A:middle
So, we're going to use

00:40:28.796 --> 00:40:31.326 A:middle
accessibilityActivationPoint

00:40:32.026 --> 00:40:33.726 A:middle
which is the point that tells

00:40:33.726 --> 00:40:35.106 A:middle
VoiceOver when a pass-through

00:40:35.106 --> 00:40:38.666 A:middle
occurs, what part of the UI do

00:40:38.666 --> 00:40:40.336 A:middle
you actually want to hook into.

00:40:40.946 --> 00:40:43.456 A:middle
So, for instance, if we have our

00:40:43.456 --> 00:40:45.986 A:middle
slider view where we have some

00:40:45.986 --> 00:40:48.336 A:middle
sort of slider nub then we can

00:40:48.336 --> 00:40:49.026 A:middle
override

00:40:49.026 --> 00:40:51.016 A:middle
accessibilityActivationPoint to

00:40:51.016 --> 00:40:52.376 A:middle
be the center of that nub so

00:40:52.626 --> 00:40:54.966 A:middle
that whenever the user passes

00:40:54.966 --> 00:40:57.196 A:middle
through that gesture it will

00:40:57.196 --> 00:40:58.636 A:middle
hook into the center of the nub

00:40:58.636 --> 00:40:59.606 A:middle
and start sliding there.

00:41:00.866 --> 00:41:04.736 A:middle
Next, we have custom scrolling,

00:41:05.266 --> 00:41:09.096 A:middle
so you may have views that have

00:41:09.506 --> 00:41:10.936 A:middle
swipe gestures on them that you

00:41:10.936 --> 00:41:12.926 A:middle
can use to get to different

00:41:12.926 --> 00:41:13.616 A:middle
parts of the UI.

00:41:13.616 --> 00:41:15.596 A:middle
For instance, in photos if I

00:41:15.596 --> 00:41:17.166 A:middle
swipe up then I get to my

00:41:17.166 --> 00:41:17.916 A:middle
details.

00:41:18.656 --> 00:41:20.546 A:middle
And there's a way that we can

00:41:20.546 --> 00:41:21.866 A:middle
get this behavior for VoiceOver

00:41:21.866 --> 00:41:22.666 A:middle
users as well.

00:41:24.136 --> 00:41:26.066 A:middle
It's called an

00:41:26.066 --> 00:41:27.826 A:middle
accessibilityScroll, it's

00:41:27.826 --> 00:41:29.296 A:middle
initiated by scrolling with

00:41:29.296 --> 00:41:31.296 A:middle
three fingers when VoiceOver is

00:41:31.296 --> 00:41:31.686 A:middle
on.

00:41:32.316 --> 00:41:33.616 A:middle
And it returns a Boolean to

00:41:33.616 --> 00:41:35.176 A:middle
indicate whether or not the

00:41:35.176 --> 00:41:36.316 A:middle
scroll was successful.

00:41:36.676 --> 00:41:37.946 A:middle
And it passes through a

00:41:37.946 --> 00:41:40.216 A:middle
direction so that you can change

00:41:40.216 --> 00:41:41.226 A:middle
the behavior based on what

00:41:41.226 --> 00:41:43.066 A:middle
direction the user is scrolling.

00:41:44.736 --> 00:41:46.186 A:middle
So, for example with our image

00:41:46.186 --> 00:41:47.676 A:middle
view if we wanted to show

00:41:47.676 --> 00:41:48.996 A:middle
details like we do in the Photos

00:41:48.996 --> 00:41:52.106 A:middle
app we'd have some property that

00:41:52.106 --> 00:41:53.276 A:middle
tells us whether or not we can

00:41:53.276 --> 00:41:54.836 A:middle
currently show the details and

00:41:54.946 --> 00:41:57.286 A:middle
we have code that actually goes

00:41:57.286 --> 00:41:58.676 A:middle
through and shows those details.

00:41:59.136 --> 00:42:00.826 A:middle
And so, what we're going to do

00:42:00.876 --> 00:42:02.786 A:middle
is override accessibilityScroll,

00:42:03.436 --> 00:42:05.966 A:middle
we're going to check can we show

00:42:05.966 --> 00:42:08.676 A:middle
our details and are we scrolling

00:42:08.676 --> 00:42:11.096 A:middle
in the right position or

00:42:11.096 --> 00:42:11.596 A:middle
direction.

00:42:12.336 --> 00:42:15.166 A:middle
And if we do we're going to show

00:42:15.166 --> 00:42:16.806 A:middle
our details and return true,

00:42:17.946 --> 00:42:20.716 A:middle
otherwise we're going to return

00:42:20.716 --> 00:42:21.136 A:middle
false.

00:42:21.496 --> 00:42:23.346 A:middle
And when I return false

00:42:23.616 --> 00:42:25.126 A:middle
VoiceOver is going to make a

00:42:25.126 --> 00:42:26.926 A:middle
bonking noise to indicate to the

00:42:26.926 --> 00:42:29.366 A:middle
user that whatever swipe that

00:42:29.366 --> 00:42:30.696 A:middle
they just did was not a valid

00:42:30.696 --> 00:42:31.026 A:middle
swipe.

00:42:31.836 --> 00:42:35.876 A:middle
Now I'm not going to go through

00:42:36.166 --> 00:42:37.666 A:middle
actually adding all those things

00:42:37.666 --> 00:42:40.416 A:middle
into our sample app, but they

00:42:40.416 --> 00:42:41.806 A:middle
are in the finished version of

00:42:41.806 --> 00:42:43.606 A:middle
the sample which you can find

00:42:43.606 --> 00:42:45.516 A:middle
and download at this URL.

00:42:46.136 --> 00:42:47.206 A:middle
And I recommend that you go and

00:42:47.206 --> 00:42:48.976 A:middle
check it out and see how that

00:42:48.976 --> 00:42:50.536 A:middle
code is implemented and see how

00:42:50.536 --> 00:42:51.956 A:middle
it works in action, play around

00:42:51.956 --> 00:42:52.476 A:middle
with it yourself.

00:42:54.416 --> 00:42:56.506 A:middle
Instead, I'd like to spend a

00:42:56.506 --> 00:42:58.416 A:middle
little bit of time talking about

00:42:58.416 --> 00:42:58.986 A:middle
Drag-and-Drop.

00:42:59.296 --> 00:43:02.256 A:middle
So, for those of you that missed

00:43:02.256 --> 00:43:04.356 A:middle
it at the keynote we unveiled

00:43:04.766 --> 00:43:06.186 A:middle
Drag-and-Drop finally coming to

00:43:06.346 --> 00:43:09.416 A:middle
iOS where I can drag pieces of

00:43:09.416 --> 00:43:11.146 A:middle
content and drop it in other

00:43:11.146 --> 00:43:12.426 A:middle
places in the interface.

00:43:12.586 --> 00:43:14.126 A:middle
For instance, if I have photos

00:43:14.126 --> 00:43:16.256 A:middle
open next to notes I can drag a

00:43:16.256 --> 00:43:18.656 A:middle
photo and drop it into one of my

00:43:18.656 --> 00:43:19.116 A:middle
notes.

00:43:20.246 --> 00:43:22.376 A:middle
Now because this was just

00:43:22.376 --> 00:43:24.486 A:middle
unveiled two days ago I don't

00:43:24.486 --> 00:43:26.106 A:middle
really expect all of you to

00:43:26.106 --> 00:43:27.786 A:middle
already understand how that API

00:43:27.876 --> 00:43:28.196 A:middle
works.

00:43:29.676 --> 00:43:31.136 A:middle
But there are just two key

00:43:31.136 --> 00:43:32.456 A:middle
concepts that you need to

00:43:32.456 --> 00:43:33.766 A:middle
understand before I talk about

00:43:33.766 --> 00:43:36.336 A:middle
the accessibility and that's

00:43:36.336 --> 00:43:38.646 A:middle
drag sources and drop points.

00:43:39.296 --> 00:43:41.266 A:middle
So, drag sources are all the

00:43:41.266 --> 00:43:43.186 A:middle
points on my view that I can

00:43:43.186 --> 00:43:45.476 A:middle
initiate a drag from and drop

00:43:45.476 --> 00:43:46.896 A:middle
points conversely are all the

00:43:46.896 --> 00:43:48.416 A:middle
places on my view that I can

00:43:48.416 --> 00:43:49.136 A:middle
drop content.

00:43:49.886 --> 00:43:53.076 A:middle
So, for instance, on the Home

00:43:53.076 --> 00:43:54.686 A:middle
screen which now uses

00:43:54.686 --> 00:43:56.116 A:middle
Drag-and-Drop for rearranging

00:43:56.116 --> 00:44:00.496 A:middle
icons I have three drop points

00:44:00.626 --> 00:44:03.026 A:middle
for each app when I'm moving

00:44:03.026 --> 00:44:03.346 A:middle
another.

00:44:03.976 --> 00:44:05.896 A:middle
The first is the left drop point

00:44:06.576 --> 00:44:10.726 A:middle
which allows me to drop the app

00:44:10.726 --> 00:44:11.936 A:middle
I'm currently moving to the left

00:44:11.936 --> 00:44:12.976 A:middle
and shift everything else to the

00:44:12.976 --> 00:44:13.286 A:middle
right.

00:44:13.286 --> 00:44:16.306 A:middle
I have the center drop point

00:44:16.306 --> 00:44:18.016 A:middle
that will create a folder

00:44:18.016 --> 00:44:19.116 A:middle
between the two apps.

00:44:19.336 --> 00:44:20.846 A:middle
And I have the right drop point

00:44:20.846 --> 00:44:23.256 A:middle
that will drop my current app to

00:44:23.256 --> 00:44:23.646 A:middle
the right.

00:44:24.236 --> 00:44:28.156 A:middle
And we need a way of describing

00:44:28.466 --> 00:44:31.376 A:middle
those different drag sources and

00:44:31.376 --> 00:44:33.136 A:middle
drop points to our VoiceOver

00:44:33.136 --> 00:44:33.686 A:middle
users.

00:44:33.886 --> 00:44:35.846 A:middle
And to do that we're going to

00:44:35.846 --> 00:44:37.566 A:middle
use this new API

00:44:38.196 --> 00:44:39.396 A:middle
accessibilityDrag

00:44:39.396 --> 00:44:40.876 A:middle
SourcesDescriptors and

00:44:40.876 --> 00:44:42.266 A:middle
accessibilityDrop

00:44:42.266 --> 00:44:43.236 A:middle
PointDescriptors.

00:44:43.786 --> 00:44:44.956 A:middle
They're arrays of

00:44:44.956 --> 00:44:45.966 A:middle
UIAccessibility

00:44:45.966 --> 00:44:48.216 A:middle
LocationDescriptor that

00:44:48.676 --> 00:44:50.136 A:middle
described the drags and the

00:44:50.136 --> 00:44:51.126 A:middle
drops for review.

00:44:52.106 --> 00:44:55.176 A:middle
So, we create a UIAccessibility

00:44:55.276 --> 00:44:57.196 A:middle
LocationDescriptor for each

00:44:57.196 --> 00:44:57.826 A:middle
drag-and-drop.

00:44:58.596 --> 00:45:00.966 A:middle
The view is going to be the view

00:45:00.966 --> 00:45:02.916 A:middle
that has the drag or drop

00:45:02.916 --> 00:45:04.396 A:middle
interaction associated with it.

00:45:05.006 --> 00:45:08.576 A:middle
The point is the point where the

00:45:08.576 --> 00:45:09.876 A:middle
drag is initiated from or the

00:45:09.876 --> 00:45:11.236 A:middle
drop is associated with.

00:45:11.716 --> 00:45:13.856 A:middle
And the name is meant to

00:45:13.856 --> 00:45:16.136 A:middle
describe what that drag or drop

00:45:16.276 --> 00:45:16.776 A:middle
does.

00:45:17.116 --> 00:45:18.486 A:middle
And there's even an attributed

00:45:18.486 --> 00:45:20.576 A:middle
name where you can use all those

00:45:20.576 --> 00:45:21.716 A:middle
attributed keys that I was

00:45:21.716 --> 00:45:23.546 A:middle
referring to earlier to tweak

00:45:23.546 --> 00:45:25.846 A:middle
the way that VoiceOver describes

00:45:26.556 --> 00:45:28.826 A:middle
the name of the descriptor.

00:45:29.806 --> 00:45:31.026 A:middle
So, let's take a look at how

00:45:31.026 --> 00:45:31.956 A:middle
this works in code.

00:45:33.006 --> 00:45:34.176 A:middle
Now this is just a hypothetical

00:45:34.176 --> 00:45:35.346 A:middle
example this isn't an actually

00:45:35.346 --> 00:45:36.056 A:middle
springboard code.

00:45:36.856 --> 00:45:38.016 A:middle
But let's say that I was

00:45:38.016 --> 00:45:40.736 A:middle
implementing rearranging apps

00:45:41.036 --> 00:45:42.816 A:middle
and I have a method that returns

00:45:43.116 --> 00:45:44.516 A:middle
an app view for a given index

00:45:44.516 --> 00:45:44.726 A:middle
path.

00:45:46.096 --> 00:45:47.026 A:middle
Well I'm going to start by

00:45:47.026 --> 00:45:48.926 A:middle
initializing that app view and

00:45:48.926 --> 00:45:50.816 A:middle
then I'm going to create a drag

00:45:50.816 --> 00:45:52.696 A:middle
descriptor and I'm going to give

00:45:52.696 --> 00:45:55.086 A:middle
it the name drag whatever the

00:45:55.086 --> 00:45:56.446 A:middle
app name is because that's what

00:45:56.446 --> 00:45:56.856 A:middle
I'm doing.

00:45:57.456 --> 00:45:59.116 A:middle
And then the center of where the

00:45:59.116 --> 00:46:00.866 A:middle
app is dragged from or sorry the

00:46:00.866 --> 00:46:01.796 A:middle
point where the app is dragged

00:46:01.796 --> 00:46:03.126 A:middle
from is its center.

00:46:04.026 --> 00:46:05.496 A:middle
And the view that actually has

00:46:05.496 --> 00:46:07.036 A:middle
that drag interaction is myself.

00:46:07.806 --> 00:46:10.866 A:middle
Then I'm going to override the

00:46:10.866 --> 00:46:12.456 A:middle
app view's drag source

00:46:12.456 --> 00:46:14.436 A:middle
descriptors to include that new

00:46:14.626 --> 00:46:15.336 A:middle
drag descriptor.

00:46:15.656 --> 00:46:17.756 A:middle
Now let's look at the drops.

00:46:18.916 --> 00:46:20.716 A:middle
So, first of all, we need to

00:46:20.716 --> 00:46:22.696 A:middle
identify the points on my app

00:46:22.696 --> 00:46:24.586 A:middle
view where I actually want to

00:46:24.586 --> 00:46:25.726 A:middle
use the drop, the left and the

00:46:25.726 --> 00:46:26.956 A:middle
right point, I know where the

00:46:26.956 --> 00:46:27.686 A:middle
center is already.

00:46:27.686 --> 00:46:30.476 A:middle
And I'm going to create a

00:46:30.476 --> 00:46:31.676 A:middle
descriptor for each of those.

00:46:32.106 --> 00:46:33.676 A:middle
My leftDescriptor I'm going to

00:46:33.676 --> 00:46:35.456 A:middle
say drop left of blank,

00:46:36.686 --> 00:46:38.556 A:middle
folderDescriptor I'm going to

00:46:38.556 --> 00:46:40.416 A:middle
say create a folder with the app

00:46:41.286 --> 00:46:43.006 A:middle
and the rightDescriptor drop

00:46:43.006 --> 00:46:43.706 A:middle
right of the app.

00:46:44.246 --> 00:46:46.366 A:middle
And then I'm going to override

00:46:46.366 --> 00:46:47.416 A:middle
accessibilityDrop

00:46:47.416 --> 00:46:49.196 A:middle
PointDescriptors to include all

00:46:49.196 --> 00:46:51.826 A:middle
those new descriptors and I'll

00:46:51.826 --> 00:46:52.646 A:middle
return my app view.

00:46:52.926 --> 00:46:55.686 A:middle
And that's it, pretty simple.

00:46:56.276 --> 00:46:59.176 A:middle
But important to convey for the

00:46:59.176 --> 00:47:00.696 A:middle
VoiceOver user what each of your

00:47:00.696 --> 00:47:02.196 A:middle
Drag-and-Drop interactions are

00:47:02.196 --> 00:47:02.576 A:middle
like.

00:47:02.976 --> 00:47:04.606 A:middle
So, if you're going to implement

00:47:04.606 --> 00:47:06.936 A:middle
this feature then please take

00:47:06.936 --> 00:47:08.216 A:middle
the time to do the accessibility

00:47:08.216 --> 00:47:11.026 A:middle
for it as well.

00:47:12.726 --> 00:47:14.936 A:middle
Now I talked about a lot of

00:47:14.936 --> 00:47:16.896 A:middle
stuff today, we looked at some

00:47:16.896 --> 00:47:19.446 A:middle
new features, we looked at

00:47:19.446 --> 00:47:20.946 A:middle
auditing your own app for

00:47:20.946 --> 00:47:23.466 A:middle
accessibility, and we looked at

00:47:23.466 --> 00:47:25.156 A:middle
various portions of our API to

00:47:25.156 --> 00:47:26.506 A:middle
solve the problems that you find

00:47:26.506 --> 00:47:27.126 A:middle
while auditing.

00:47:27.856 --> 00:47:30.416 A:middle
And that's all great technical

00:47:30.416 --> 00:47:32.506 A:middle
stuff, but I want to bring it

00:47:32.506 --> 00:47:35.096 A:middle
back to the beginning to remind

00:47:35.096 --> 00:47:37.056 A:middle
you why we're all actually in

00:47:37.056 --> 00:47:37.596 A:middle
this room.

00:47:39.126 --> 00:47:42.146 A:middle
Accessibility is about people,

00:47:43.936 --> 00:47:46.696 A:middle
the common person's life is

00:47:46.756 --> 00:47:49.456 A:middle
enhanced by technology, but for

00:47:49.456 --> 00:47:51.656 A:middle
people with disabilities it's

00:47:51.656 --> 00:47:52.416 A:middle
transformative.

00:47:53.806 --> 00:47:55.486 A:middle
Accessible technology enables

00:47:55.486 --> 00:47:57.466 A:middle
people to live their lives the

00:47:57.466 --> 00:48:00.336 A:middle
way that they want to, to

00:48:00.336 --> 00:48:02.746 A:middle
accomplish goals and tasks that

00:48:02.746 --> 00:48:06.246 A:middle
were once unattainable, to have

00:48:06.246 --> 00:48:08.026 A:middle
jobs and roles in their

00:48:08.026 --> 00:48:10.276 A:middle
communities that they couldn't

00:48:10.276 --> 00:48:13.596 A:middle
have had before, and to interact

00:48:13.596 --> 00:48:15.136 A:middle
with the world in ways that were

00:48:15.136 --> 00:48:16.396 A:middle
once impossible.

00:48:17.206 --> 00:48:21.196 A:middle
The work that you do to ensure

00:48:21.196 --> 00:48:23.066 A:middle
that your apps work for everyone

00:48:23.446 --> 00:48:24.226 A:middle
is critical.

00:48:25.056 --> 00:48:28.006 A:middle
So, we thank you for the amazing

00:48:28.006 --> 00:48:29.756 A:middle
work that you've already done,

00:48:29.986 --> 00:48:31.796 A:middle
that you will continue to do,

00:48:31.976 --> 00:48:34.556 A:middle
and that you will start today as

00:48:34.556 --> 00:48:36.546 A:middle
we work together to make Apple's

00:48:36.546 --> 00:48:38.096 A:middle
